Package: gnome-doc-utils
Version: 0.16.1
Revision: 3
Depends: <<
	libgettext3-shlibs,
	libiconv,
	libxml2-bin (>= 2.6.32-1),
	libxml2-py26,
	libxml2-shlibs (>= 2.6.32-1),
	libxslt-bin (>= 1.1.1-1),
	libxslt-shlibs (>= 1.1.14-1),
	python26,
	rarian-compat
<<
BuildDepends: <<
	autoconf (>= 2.60),
	automake1.10,
	fink (>= 0.24.12),
	gettext-bin,
	gettext-tools,
	intltool40,
	libgettext3-dev,
	libiconv-dev,
	libtool2,
	libxml2 (>= 2.6.32-1),
	libxslt (>= 1.1.14-1),
	pkgconfig (>= 0.23)
<<
Replaces: yelp (<< 2.10.0-1)
Source: mirror:gnome:sources/%n/0.16/%n-%v.tar.bz2
Source-MD5: 85d4bba44773f6162de72e81e8bd0ab0
ConfigureParams: --mandir=%p/share/man --disable-scrollkeeper --disable-dependency-tracking
NoSetMAKEFLAGS: true
SetMAKEFLAGS: -j1
PatchFile: %n.patch
PatchFile-MD5: c758f1aedcf964e55ca782572d4770af
#PatchScript: perl -pi -e 's/-I m4/-I m4 -I tools/' Makefile.am
CompileScript: <<
	autoreconf -f -i
	PYTHON=%p/bin/python2.6 ./configure %c
	# you can ignore the above 'chmod' warnings
	make
<<
InstallScript: make install DESTDIR=%d
DocFiles: AUTHORS COPYING* ChangeLog po/ChangeLog:ChangeLog.po xml2po/ChangeLog:ChangeLog.xml2po NEWS README xml2po/TODO:TODO.xml2po
PostInstScript: <<
	if [ configure = "$1" ]; then
		scrollkeeper-update -q
	fi
<<
PostRmScript: <<  
	if [ remove != "$1" ]; then
		scrollkeeper-update -q
	fi
<<
Description: Tools and templates for Gnome documentation
DescDetail: <<
	gnome-doc-utils is a collection of documentation utilities for the
	Gnome project. Notably, it contains utilities for building
	documentation and all auxiliary files in your source tree, and it
	contains the DocBook XSLT stylesheets that were once distributed
	with Yelp.
<<
DescPackaging: <<
	Redo autotools so that @datarootdir@ is substituted in *.pc
	because upstream doesn't want to fix it. See:
	http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=313610
	http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=342327

	Add missing ACLOCAL flag. See:
	http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=482017

	Patch (thanks pogma!) to avoid lots of ./configure noise about
	chmod in tools. Bug in autoconf? See:
	http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=557732
<<
